node.text:
Waterproof boy 🦎

📽 @simplygecko.co

This is a really cool aspect of gecko skin. The water is not actually touching their scales, but is coming into contact with air that is trapped in between tiny hair follicles called spinules. These follicles suspend the water so they can't flatten out over the surface area of the skin. They are less than a thousandth of a millimeter apart, and make geckos almost waterproof.

node.text:
In Love with United Kingdom 🥰🇬🇧

Places and photos by:
1. Windsor Castle @piteshmistry
2. Cadgwith Cove @whatstacydid
3. Corston, Wiltshire @steve_parke
4. Edensor @fayazey
5. North Yorkshire @hope_and_wander
6. Isle of Wight @shadedcream
7. Burford @lensereflection
8. Blaise Hamlet @adamjason1
9. Bibury @the_onlycookiemonster
10. Stow on the Wold, Cotswolds @whatstacydid

The United Kingdom, made up of England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland, is an island nation in northwestern Europe.

England – birthplace of Shakespeare and The Beatles –

is home to the capital, London, a globally influential centre of finance and culture.

England is also site of Neolithic Stonehenge, Bath’s Roman spa and centuries-old universities at Oxford and Cambridge. ❤🇬🇧

Hey little guy! @animaledventures show us the pouch, that acts as a warm, safe place for joeys. 🙏🏽

📽 @animaledventures 🦘

At around six months, when a baby kangaroo is sufficiently well developed, it will leave the pouch for short periods, returning when it needs to feed. Did you know that?
